==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mysterious
<hw>Mys*te"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>myst⟦egrave⟧rieux</ets>. See 1st <er>Mystery</er>.]</ety> <def>Of
or pertaining to mystery; containing a mystery; difficult or impossible
to understand; inexplicable; obscure; not revealed or explained;
enigmatical; incomprehensible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God at last⟦br⟧
To Satan, first in sin, his doom applied,⟦br⟧
Thought in <qex>mysterious</qex> terms.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Obscure; secret; occult; dark; mystic;
cabalistic; enigmatical; unintelligible; inexplicable;
incomprehensible.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mysteriously</ent>⟦br⟧
